CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 10, 1959, pg. A2 reads: "So-Re-Lit Aids NAACP - The So-Re-Lit Club presented the Pittsburgh branch of the NAACP with a check for $100 in partial payment of a life membership, at the recent membership meeting. Above are Mrs. Carrie Harley, Mrs. Florence Bolden, Mrs. Jayne Gautt [Gantt] Davis, president, and Mrs. Mary Jane Wood, treasurer.  Receiving the check is John Gary Jones, local NAACP treasurer. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: So-Re-Lit Club members Carrie Harley, Florence Bolden, Jayne Gantt Davis, and Mary Jane Wood, presenting check to John Gary Jones, standing in Ebenezer Baptist church during NAACP membership meeting
